      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AGENT TWENTY ONE (1) boasts a strong record this journey with three wins and three minors from six tries. Comes off a (16.91) win last time, scoring by 1.75 lengths in a Grade 6 over 300m at Murray Bridge. With a clean break looks hard to beat. DANYO'S HENRY (2) was midfield throughout and finished there last time when 5th (16.89) at Murray Bridge. Solid record here at this trip including two wins. Has good early burn and is drawn to be prominent. Better than last start and can bounce back. PARRAKIE (5) was an impressive winner last time, overcoming a check to score by 4 lengths in a Grade 6 over 300m at this track. Can measure up again. RITZA BENJI (4) jumps at a shorter distance and still warrants respect.",
